data.description: This home will check all your boxes.  Well maintained 3 bedroom, 2 bath home on just over an acre with a 20x20 workshop in the back yard.  Home has been remodeled to create an open floor plan for living space but also has split floor plan for privacy.  All kitchen and bathroom cabinets are custom made by the owner.  The kitchen has so many cabinets, your gourmet side will certainly shine. Stove is propane and electric so you can cook even during a power outage.  Granite countertops with large island finish the space very nicely in the open plan. Living spaces are oversized and there is lots of closet space for storage.  AC was replaced in 2020 with a 3-ton unit, Propane hot water tank was installed in 2020.  Roof is in great condition but seller will give $10,000 credit toward next replacement. There is a dog washing/trimming station in the garage. Storm shutters installed in 2004 and add a nice look to the outside.  The yard has the old Florida look with several live oaks which spread lots of shade for those lazy afternoons. The woodshop has a dust removal system for all your woodworking needs.  There is a pergola next to the Florida room with a large stone paver floor.  This is inside a fenced area behind the home where your fur babies or grandbabies can play safely.  This home has so much to offer and is just waiting for the right owner.  Low POA (property owners' association) fee of $236 PER YEAR get you access to private member River Park where you can swim or launch your kayak, canoe, tube or paddleboard.  Space for picnics or just hanging out.  Community center also included in annual fee which includes pool, tennis courts, pickleball courts, basketball, horseshoes, shuffleboard, bocce and disc golf.  Amazing value!
